parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster/actuator can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual before the brakes engage
the brakes make a loud whirring or grinding noise
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of power, inability to start the engine, and malfunctioning of essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: brake pedal feeling heavy or less responsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The soy-based wiring material can attract rodents, causing damage to the electrical system, which can lead to costly repairs and potentially cause safety issues.
symptoms: Rodent damage to the electrical system
attraction of rodents to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or loss of control, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal feeling soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and hybrid system can cause loss of power, stalling, or inability to start the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine revving when idling on cruise control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
The glare on the navigation screen can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Unreadable navigation screen in bright sunlight
distractions while driving to read the screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to shut down or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The instrument panel displays a "Hybrid System Failure" message
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly and unexpectedly
and may not respond to braking attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and gear shift issues can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to loss of control or unexpected movement.
symptoms: The vehicle may lunge forward or backward
and the gear shift lever may not accurately indicate the gear position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system malfunctions can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to loss of control or unexpected movement.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience electrical system failures
such as the failure of the power train
and may display warning messages or lights on the instrument panel.
